OL,4,CReview bid after right-wing extremist
OL,5,C'told to read classic books'
OL,6, The Attorney General has been asked to
OL,7, review a sentence given to a right-wing
OL,8, extremist for a terrorism offence.
OL,10,FBen John was handed the 24-month
OL,11,Fsentence, suspended for two years, at
OL,12,FLeicester Crown Court on Tuesday.
OL,14,FAccording to media reports, the
OL,15,F21-year-old was also ordered by a judge
OL,16,Fto read classic novels such as Pride
OL,17,Fand Prejudice and to return to court in
OL,18,FJanuary.
OL,20,FIn a letter, campaign group Hope Not
OL,21,FHate asked for a review of the case.
